                        "type": "1",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "<p>Which interventions by the nurse are beneficial for the postpartum client who is progressing toward the taking-hold phase? Select all that apply.</p>",
                        "subjectId": "748251aedc42d4333c5d8a7d10bd5441",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "<p>Rationales</p><p><br></p><p>Option 1:During the taking-in phase in the postpartum client, the nurse should provide positive reinforcement of appropriate behaviors to the client.</p><p>Option 2:While progressing toward the taking-hold phase, the nurse should provide discharge education to the client to prevent any complications.</p><p>Option 3:In the taking-hold phase, the nurse should teach the client about methods for comforting the infant.</p><p>Option 4:While progressing toward the taking-hold phase, the nurse should encourage the client to increase infant contact. This helps to develop positive bonding of the client with the infant.</p><p>Option 5:The nurse should encourage the client and her family members to participate in self-care and infant care. This helps in maintaining good health in the client and the infant.</p><p><br></p><p>Test Taking Tips: The key word is \"progressing\" toward the taking-hold phase. The client is not yet in the taking-hold phase. Answer choices that reflect the taking-in and taking-hold phases will be incorrect.</p>",
                        "id": "901e518304354e718588de22bbcdec49",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    }
